  <brief_title>Effect of Iron Therapy as an Adjunct to Epoetin Alfa in the Anemia of Cancer Chemotherapy</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multicenter, Randomized, Controlled Prospective Trial of the Safety and Efficacy of Ferrlecit® in Anemic Cancer Patients Who Are Receiving Acute Chemotherapy and Epoetin as Compared to Oral Iron and No Treatment</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Watson Pharmaceuticals</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Watson Pharmaceuticals</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates the safety and efficacy of Ferrlecit® (ferric gluconate; a form of
      intravenous iron) or ferrous sulfate (a form of oral iron) in improving the response to
      epoetin alfa among anemic cancer patients receiving chemotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
